article.headline: St. Francis, NY 73, Monmouth, N.J. 62
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. St. Francis, N.Y. 73, Monmouth 62. NEW YORK -- Ricky Cadell scored 17 of his 20 points in the second half and St. Francis, N.Y. snapped a five-game losing streak with a 73-62 victory over Monmouth on Thursday night. John Gooden added 14 points for Terriers (4-10, 2-2 Northeast Conference), while Rocco Rubino had 11. R.J. Rutledge had 19 points for the Hawks (4-13, 2-3), while Mike Myers-Keitt added 13 and Travis Taylor 11. Monmouth scored the first nine points of the game on the way to a 22-10 lead. Cadell gave the Terriers the lead for good at 35-32 when he hit a 3-pointer with 17:31 to play.
